You'd never know about this place if you weren't specifically looking for it. You'd be missing out.  That's how I learned about it...by word of mouth: a police officer friend told me the best subs in the area were here. Another friend said it was his favorite food in the District--bar none.  I moved in nearby not too long ago, and set about looking for it. I noticed the hours: 8a-3p Mon-Fri. That's it? Well, I thought, if they can stay in business this long, their sales during those hours must be tremendous. There's probably a reason for that.  Today was the day. Grabbed a G-Man to take into night shift, along with sides of olives and pepperoni & cheese. Got to work, and set about cutting it in half, because I had a feeling. A good one.  Good thing I split it--MY GOD THIS SANDWICH! I'm so happy I have more  of it to eat later. I'm going to bring a bunch of these in to work in the future; I'm wearing a cape when I do it, because I'll be proclaimed a hero.  And let's not forget to talk about the service: the folks inside are the nicest people you could meet. I told them what my friends said about their place, and they were humble, and thankful and appreciative. Getting the sandwich and sides was super quick.  Very few places at any price point live up to and exceed expectations in the entire DC/MD/VA area like Mags (as my friends call it).  Bravo!
